<subSubSection id="C35552F7FF95BF3DA5994BFF468D1B7A" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF0017CFF95BF3DA5994BFF468D1B7A" blockId="1.[151,1437,644,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF95BF3DA5994BFF43581D9B" bold="true" box="[199,324,716,742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Comment.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B270B21FF95BF3DA4144BFF46911B7A" collectionCode="R" county="And Mao'er" location="The" municipality="Anjiangping" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1" stateProvince="Guangxi" typeStatus="holotype">
The original description is based on 
<specimenCount id="9D49CAF5FF95BF3DA7844BFE41521D9B" box="[730,846,716,743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
. There were male species at that time, and the species was determined based on the characteristics of both sexes, but now because the male specimens are lost, only the female species remain, so the remaining label information cannot be entered. Comparing the 
<typeStatus id="54F4BFDEFF95BF3DA1F24A27470D1C53" box="[1196,1297,788,814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">holotype</typeStatus>
, this species is similar in general appearance and tergites characters to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF95BF3DA6404A0A41BA1C2F" authorityName="Li &amp; Li" authorityYear="2013" box="[798,934,825,850]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatinum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF95BF3DA6404A0A41BA1C2F" box="[798,934,825,850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">L. anatinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCounty id="629179F0FF95BF3DA6EC4A0B46271C2E" box="[946,1083,824,851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">And Mao’er</collectingCounty>
shan N. 
<collectionCode id="ED5E99B9FF95BF3DA1C74A0A46B31C2E" box="[1177,1199,825,851]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">R</collectionCode>
. and 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B949B06FF95BF3DA1B94A0B476F1C2F" box="[1255,1395,824,850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Anjiangping</collectingMunicipality>
are only 63 kilometers apart in the north of 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF95BF3DA7394A6F40D61C0B" box="[615,714,860,886]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, so it is considered the same species. 
<location id="8E9057A7FF95BF3DA1DE4A6F46B01C0B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E6B06AFF95BF3DA5C94B2B468D1B7A:8E9057A7FF95BF3DA1DE4A6F46B01C0B" box="[1152,1196,860,886]" county="And Mao'er" municipality="Anjiangping" name="The" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" stateProvince="Guangxi">The</location>
previously unknown female sexual characters are as follows: posterior margin of tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF95BF3DA6B34AB3465B1CE6" box="[1005,1095,896,923]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[567,1013,1056,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-290@1.[566,1021,1052,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lobrathium anatinum (A–C) and L. excisissimum (D–G). A female tergite VIII B female sternite VIII C female tergites IX–X. D male sternite VII E male sternite VIII F aedeagus in ventral view G aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm. FIGURE 2. Male habitus of Lobrathium spp. A L. biaculeatum B L. chengzhifeii C L. excisissimum. Scales: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524308/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) convex; posterior margin of sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF95BF3DA4694A9743931CC2" box="[311,399,932,959]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[567,1013,1056,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-290@1.[566,1021,1052,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lobrathium anatinum (A–C) and L. excisissimum (D–G). A female tergite VIII B female sternite VIII C female tergites IX–X. D male sternite VII E male sternite VIII F aedeagus in ventral view G aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm. FIGURE 2. Male habitus of Lobrathium spp. A L. biaculeatum B L. chengzhifeii C L. excisissimum. Scales: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524308/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) strongly convex and with moderately dense micropubescence; tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF95BF3DA1A04A97474A1CC2" box="[1278,1366,932,959]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[567,1013,1056,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-290@1.[566,1021,1052,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lobrathium anatinum (A–C) and L. excisissimum (D–G). A female tergite VIII B female sternite VIII C female tergites IX–X. D male sternite VII E male sternite VIII F aedeagus in ventral view G aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm. FIGURE 2. Male habitus of Lobrathium spp. A L. biaculeatum B L. chengzhifeii C L. excisissimum. Scales: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524308/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) with median suture and long postero-lateral processes; tergite X (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF95BF3DA6614AFB41881C9E" box="[831,916,968,995]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[567,1013,1056,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-290@1.[566,1021,1052,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lobrathium anatinum (A–C) and L. excisissimum (D–G). A female tergite VIII B female sternite VIII C female tergites IX–X. D male sternite VII E male sternite VIII F aedeagus in ventral view G aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm. FIGURE 2. Male habitus of Lobrathium spp. A L. biaculeatum B L. chengzhifeii C L. excisissimum. Scales: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524308/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) nearly reaching anterior margin of tergite IX (
